&s;hall be explained.'</Q></P>
<P>Standfa&s;t, who had taken good time to &s;ort his cards, began
now to con&s;ider how he &s;hould play his game; and knowing the major's
credulity to his &s;tronge&s;t &s;uit, after &s;tipulating for a patient
hear|ing, he thus began.</P>
<P> 
<Q REND="inline">'You very well know, major, you are upwards of
&s;eventy; whereas your lady is not more than twenty-five. She married you
